<div id="review_3556306870" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3556306870" />
    <a title="Emma Garland" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/71917659-emma-garland"><img alt="Emma Garland" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1573142049p2/71917659.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3556306870?book_show_action=true">Sep 26, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emma Garland" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emma Garland" href="/user/show/71917659-emma-garland">Emma Garland</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/42249612-here-to-stay">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3556306870" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10458832961019685020">When Gemma stumbles upon Elliott during an open garden day, she stops to admire his beautiful house. They begin to chat and swiftly fall in love. A whirlwind wedding in Vegas later and everything is going swimmingly. That is until the in laws invite themselves to stay. <br/><br/>Rolling up shortly after with Gemma’s younger sister Chloe in tow, they soon begin to wreak havoc. Her parents are utter slobs and Chloe is supposedly ill, locked away in her room. Just when Elliott thinks he cant take anymore, si</span>
  <span id="freeText10458832961019685020" style="display:none">When Gemma stumbles upon Elliott during an open garden day, she stops to admire his beautiful house. They begin to chat and swiftly fall in love. A whirlwind wedding in Vegas later and everything is going swimmingly. That is until the in laws invite themselves to stay. <br /><br />Rolling up shortly after with Gemma’s younger sister Chloe in tow, they soon begin to wreak havoc. Her parents are utter slobs and Chloe is supposedly ill, locked away in her room. Just when Elliott thinks he cant take anymore, sinister things begin to happen. Far more serious than a sink left full of dishes. What exactly has Elliott got himself into? <br /><br />This is absolutely bonkers. The beginning was a little blah di blah with a fairly weak connection between the main characters. It wasn’t until her family arrived that it progressed into something I couldn’t put down. It’s infuriating in places and I spent most of the book preying for a good dose of karma. Crazy, far fetched and addictive. 4 stars from me. ✨ </span>
  <a data-text-id="10458832961019685020" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


